n Hahn took full credit—and the 1944 Nobel Prize—for the work they had done together on nuclear fission. Ruth Sime's absorbing book is the definitive biography of Lise Meitner, the story of a brilliant woman whose extraordinary life illustrates not only the dramatic scientific progress but also the injustice and destruction that have marked the twentieth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aWomen physicistszAustriavBiography. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  a20th century.  abiographical.  acareer.  achemistry.  aconcentration camp.  afemale scientist.  afeminism.  afeminist.  ainjustice.  aintellectual property.  ajewish heritage.  ajewish women.  ajudaism.  anazi germany.  anobel prize.  anuclear fission.  anuclear physics.  arefugee.  arole model.  ascientific.  asexism.  asexist.  astrong women.  atrue story.  awomen in history.  awomen in stem.  awomen in the workforce.  aworld history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052008906840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052091899340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520918993423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520918993/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY